{{Coord|24|14|50.5|N|120|41|56.5|E|display=title}} {{Infobox building |name = Taiwan Balloons Museum |native_name = 台灣氣球博物館 |image = |opening = |location = [[Shengang District|Shengang]], [[Taichung]], [[Taiwan]] |building_type = [[Museum]] |start_date = |completion_date = |cost = |roof = |top_floor = |architectural = |observatory = |floor_count = |floor_area = |elevator_count = |architect = |structural_engineer = |main_contractor = |management = [[Taiwan Tailloon Balloons]] Co., Ltd<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.culture.tw/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=2126&Itemid=156 |title=Taiwan Culture Portal - Taiwan Balloons Museum blends fun and industrial heritage |publisher=Culture.tw |date=2011-09-28 |accessdate=23 February 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130918235750/http://www.culture.tw/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=2126&Itemid=156 |archivedate=18 September 2013 |df= }}</ref> |owner = Taiwan Tailloon Balloons Co., Ltd |website = [http://www.prolloon.com.tw/ www.prolloon.com.tw] |references = }}
The '''Taiwan Balloons Museum''' ({{zh|c=台灣氣球博物館|p=Táiwān Qìqiú Bówùguǎn}}) is a [[museum]] about [[balloon]]s in Anli Village, [[Shengang District]], [[Taichung]], [[Taiwan]]. The museum is owned and operated by [[Taiwan Tailloon Balloons]] Co., Ltd.<ref name="taiwanfun.com">{{cite web|url=http://www.taiwanfun.com/central/taichung/recreation/0802/0802Balloons.htm|date=February 2008|title=Taiwan Balloons Museum|website=Compass Taichung City Guide|accessdate=9 May 2017}}</ref>
==History== The museum building were once the old factory of the Taiwan Tailloon Balloons Co., Ltd. The current factory of the company is located right next to the museum building.
==Architecture== The museum building resembles a balloon from outside.<ref name="taiwanfun.com"/>
==Exhibitions== The museum exhibits the balloon production process, balloon making activities and balloon-related games.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://eng.taichung.gov.tw/ct.aspx?xItem=11711&ctNode=4352&mp=99|title=Taiwan Balloons Museum|website=Taichung City Government|accessdate=9 May 2017}}</ref>
==Transportation== The museum is accessible west from [[Fengyuan Station]] of the [[Taiwan Railways Administration]].{{fact|date=February 2014}}
